[44.90021, "o", "\u001b[4;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[1;96m+\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 3 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(38603 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(15.8s)\u001b[0m\u001b[5;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mIter 1-2 done: dossier bootstrapped at \u001b[0m\u001b[6;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m`.brainyard/agents/research-agent/add-format-text-json-option-cli/` with 3 acceptance criteria \u001b[0m\u001b[7;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m(a1=explore map, a2=plan blueprint, a3=recommendation summary). Next move per heuristic 2 \u001b[0m\u001b[8;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m(well-scoped, but RECOMMEND-only so we stop before exec): A (EXPLORE) → B (PLAN-AUTHOR) → F/H \u001b[0m\u001b[9;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m(synthesize + finalize). Now: move A. Invoke explore-agent to map how greetings are currently \u001b[0m\u001b[10;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mformatted and rendered across the project files — output functions, render sites, existing CLI arg \u001b[0m\u001b[11;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mparsing. Pass the research dossier path in :agent-context per the contract. I'll dispatch via clojure \u001b[0m\u001b[12;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mfence so I can capture the returned path for logging next.\u001b[0m\u001b[13;1H\u001b[2K  "]
[44.900233, "o", "\u001b[2m• Code:\u001b[0m\u001b[14;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\u001b[15;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def explore-result\u001b[0m\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m  (explore-agent\u001b[0m\u001b[17;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m    {:question \"Map how greetings are CURRENTLY formatted and rendered across this CLI project. Identify,\u001b[0m\u001b[18;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mwith file path + line citations: (1) every function/site that produces or formats a greeting string, (2)\u001b[0m\u001b[19;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mevery site that renders/prints greeting output to the user, (3) the existing CLI argument parsing setup\u001b[0m\u001b[20;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(where flags/options are defined and dispatched), and (4) any existing notion of output format. Goal is\u001b[0m\u001b[21;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mto understand all touch points a new --format {text,json} option would need to thread through. Read-only\u001b[0m\u001b[22;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35msurvey — do not propose changes.\"\u001b[0m\u001b[23;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m     :agent-context \"Research dossier:\u001b[0m\u001b[24;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m"]
[44.900289, "o", "\u001b[35m.brainyard/agents/research-agent/add-format-text-json-option-cli/dossier.md\\nPurpose: Research what it\u001b[0m\u001b[25;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mwould take to add a --format {text,json} option to this CLI (RECOMMEND only — no code\u001b[0m\u001b[26;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mwrites).\\nAcceptance focus: a1 (map all greeting format/render sites + CLI arg parsing with path+line\u001b[0m\u001b[27;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mcitations).\\nHint: Focus on greeting output functions, render/print sites, and the CLI arg-parsing layer.\u001b[0m\u001b[28;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mCite paths and line ranges so the plan specialist can reference exact touch points.\"}))\u001b[0m\u001b[29;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println explore-result)\u001b[0m\u001b[30;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\u001b[35;3H"]
