[82.824433, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\u001b[2;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(def explore-result\u001b[0m\u001b[3;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m  (explore-agent\u001b[0m\u001b[4;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m    {:question \"Map how greetings are CURRENTLY formatted and rendered across this CLI project. Identify,\u001b[0m\u001b[5;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mwith file path + line citations: (1) every function/site that produces or formats a greeting string, (2)\u001b[0m\u001b[6;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mevery site that renders/prints greeting output to the user, (3) the existing CLI argument parsing setup\u001b[0m\u001b[7;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(where flags/options are defined and dispatched), and (4) any existing notion of output format. Goal is\u001b[0m\u001b[8;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mto understand all touch points a new --format {text,json} option would need to thread through. Read-only\u001b[0m\u001b[9;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35msurvey — do not propose changes.\"\u001b[0m\u001b[10;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m     :agent-context \"Research dossier:\u001b[0m\u001b[11;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m.brainyard/agents/res"]
[82.824449, "o", "earch-agent/add-format-text-json-option-cli/dossier.md\\nPurpose: Research what it\u001b[0m\u001b[12;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mwould take to add a --format {text,json} option to this CLI (RECOMMEND only — no code\u001b[0m\u001b[13;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mwrites).\\nAcceptance focus: a1 (map all greeting format/render sites + CLI arg parsing with path+line\u001b[0m\u001b[14;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mcitations).\\nHint: Focus on greeting output functions, render/print sites, and the CLI arg-parsing layer.\u001b[0m\u001b[15;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35mCite paths and line ranges so the plan specialist can reference exact touch points.\"}))\u001b[0m\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m\u001b[35m(println explore-result)\u001b[0m\u001b[17;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\u001b[18;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[2m• Output:\u001b[0m\u001b[19;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m┌─\u001b[0m\u001b[20;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0m[detached to background after 30000ms — task-id=task-1 STILL RUNNING. DO NOT re-emit this code; the task\u001b[21;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mis in flight. Choose how to wait — pick ONE: (A) task$wakeup :task-id \"task-1\" — YIELD: acknowledge i"]
[82.824471, "o", "n\u001b[22;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mone line and END the turn; you are AUTO-RESUMED next turn when the task finishes (frees the session —\u001b[23;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mbest for a long wait). (B) task$wait :task-id \"task-1\" :timeout-ms 60000 — HOLD: block and continue THIS\u001b[24;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mturn when it finishes (best for a short wait; on timeout, wait again or switch to task$wakeup). Peek\u001b[25;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m│ \u001b[0mprogress with task$detail (add :last-n N); task$cancel to abort.]\u001b[26;1H\u001b[2K    \u001b[2m└─\u001b[0m\u001b[27;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[1m\u001b[95m subagents (1 running, 0 done) \u001b[0m\u001b[2m─────────────────────────────────────────\u001b[0m\u001b[28;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[1;96m●\u001b[0m \u001b[1;97mexplore-agent/yellow-vole-597\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m[explore-agent]\u001b[0m  \u001b[96mrunning\u001b[0m  \u001b[2mIter 3/100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(68260 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m39s\u001b[0m\u001b[29;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[task-1 moved to bac"]
