[489.374923, "o", "\u001b[1;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mcancelled. task-3 (re-dispatched plan-agent) is STILL RUNNING after a 90s hold timeout. I must not \u001b[0m\u001b[2;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mre-emit the plan-agent code. The remaining work — log the plan result, flip a2→satisfied, write \u001b[0m\u001b[3;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mverdict, finalize — all depends on task-3's output. Since holding already timed out once, the \u001b[0m\u001b[4;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mefficient move is to YIELD: park on task-3 via task$wakeup and be auto-resumed when it terminates. \u001b[0m\u001b[5;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mThis frees the session for the long wait.\u001b[0m\u001b[6;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[36m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36mtask$wakeup\u001b[0m({\"task-id\" \"task-3\", \"note\" \"plan-agent (task-3) finished...): called \u001b[2m→\u001b[0m \u001b[92mdone\u001b[0m, 3ms, 167 chars\u001b[7;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 10 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(48309 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(11.1s)\u001b[0m\u001b[8;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mI parked on task-3 (plan-agent) and was resumed, but the in-flight roster says task-3 is STILL RUNNING \u001b[0m\u001b[9;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m(age 133s). I must not re-"]
[489.37495, "o", "emit the plan-agent code. Before deciding to wait again or yield, let me \u001b[0m\u001b[10;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mpeek at task-3's status and output tail to see if it's near completion or stuck. task$detail with \u001b[0m\u001b[11;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2m:last-n is the right read-only probe.\u001b[0m\u001b[12;1H\u001b[2K  \u001b[36m→\u001b[0m \u001b[1;36mtask$detail\u001b[0m({\"task-id\" \"task-3\", \"last-n\" \"20\"}): called \u001b[2m→\u001b[0m \u001b[92mdone\u001b[0m, 0ms, 615 chars\u001b[13;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m[\u001b[0m\u001b[92m✓\u001b[0m\u001b[2m] \u001b[0m\u001b[1;97mIteration 11 / 100\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(48659 tok)\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m(25.7s)\u001b[0m\u001b[14;1H\u001b[2K\u001b[2m  Think: \u001b[0m\u001b[2mState review: task-1 (explore-agent) completed → a1 satisfied (full touch-point map). task-2 (first \u001b[0m\u001b[15;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mplan-agent) was cancelled. task-3 (re-dispatched plan-agent) is STILL RUNNING at ~144s with 0 output \u001b[0m\u001b[16;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mlines — a clojure-fence dispatch only flushes its println on completion, so 0 lines is expected \u001b[0m\u001b[17;1H\u001b[2K         \u001b[2mmid-flight. I must NOT re-emit the plan-agent code. A 90s HOLD already timed out and I've parke"]
